data.title: Engineer Spotlight | Mississippi Board of Licensure for Professional ...
data.snippet:
Rabeea W. Bazuhair, Ben C. Cox, Jesse D. Doyle, Jonathan Easterling, Jessica V. Lewis, Alex Middleton, Carl Pittman, Braden T. Smith, Abhinash Subedi, W. Griffin Sullivan."

Q5. Why is professional licensure important to you?

"Professional licensure helps protect the health, safety, and welfare of the public.  Professional licensure is also a lifelong process through which licensed professionals continue to stay current in their field.  Licensure is one of several ways that engineers and surveyors can better themselves and in turn improve people’s lives."

---

#### June 2025 Engineer Spotlight: Kayla Erickson, PE [...] "Don't worry about "figuring it out." You will always learn new information and make decisions as it comes to you. I moved from Environmental Engineering to Civil to Oceanographic Engineering, and I remember fearing that this pivoting would set me behind others who were staying true to their original course. Knowing what I do now, I wouldn't change a thing about that career path. My background is diverse, and I can approach infrastructure problems with a unique perspective. I am proud of my interdisciplinary knowledge, and I find myself invited to quite a dynamic setting that I thoroughly enjoy because of it."

Q4. What would you say to young people, who might be interested in STEM careers such as engineering or surveying? [...] Q6. Why is professional licensure important to you?

"Professional licensure is important to me because it is a foundation for my career, provides networking and growth opportunities, and ensures that I continue my education in engineering annually."

---

#### May 2025 Engineer Spotlight:  Alex Ray Price, PE

The Mississippi Board of Licensure for Professional Engineers and Surveyors would like to shine a spotlight on newly licensed Professional Engineer Alex Price.  Alex has a very diverse educational background in that he has an affiliation with several Mississippi schools including:

 Pearl River Community College
 William Carey University
 East Mississippi Community College
